HEADWORD: Thready
<hw>Thread"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Like
thread or filaments; slender; <as>as, the <ex>thready</ex> roots of a
shrub</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Containing, or consisting of, thread.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Threap</ent>⟦br⟧
